<section sectnbr = "1B">
<servcat sctnbr = "01" scnbr = "02">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENBP70A1206002" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "03" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
EVAP Canister Purge Valve Inspection
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENBP70A1206001">EVAP System Components</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<attention1>
<ptxt>
If vacuum is applied using mouth, there is a risk of inhaling harmful fuel vapor.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Be sure to use a hand vacuum pump to apply vacuum.
</ptxt>
</attention1>
<attention4>
<ptxt>
If too high a vacuum is applied, the EVAP canister purge valve may be damaged.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Do not exceed a vacuum of –66 kPa (–0.67 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, –9.57 psi, –0.66 bar).
</ptxt>
</attention4>
<s1>
<ptxt>
With ignition OFF, disconnect connector and vacuum hoses from EVAP canister purge valve.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove EVAP canister purge valve from intake manifold.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check resistance between two terminals of EVAP canister purge valve.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If faulty condition is found, replace EVAP canister purge valve.
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
EVAP canister purge valve resistance
</title>
<ptxt>
30 to 34 Ω at 20 &#176;C (68 &#176;F)
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I3RM0A120008.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "44.862mm" ver = "01" gw = "143" gh = "110"/>
</figure>
</spec>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check EVAP canister purge valve operation as follows.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If faulty condition is found, replace EVAP canister purge valve.
</ptxt>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Install special tool and vacuum hose (2) to EVAP canister purge valve (1).
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L1B003">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09917-47011">
09917–47011
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
With 12 V battery connected to EVAP canister purge valve terminals, check that vacuum (–60 kPa, –0.6 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, –8.7 psi, –0.6 bar) cannot be applied to EVAP canister purge valve.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
With no 12 V battery connected to EVAP canister purge valve terminals, check that vacuum (–60 kPa, –0.6 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, –8.7 psi, –0.6 bar) can be applied to EVAP canister purge valve.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP60B120005.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "87.888mm" ver = "03" gw = "152" gh = "233"/>
